caption: Big fan! when I lived in the neighborhood, would stop by routinely for fresh pita and labaneh -- so recommend! Even returned this week and adopted a plant they couldn't care for; such a sweet staff and manager! For other food recs, I'm in love with their mint tea, and the shwarma sandwiches are great as well.
Tasty Middle Eastern fare.  Quick and friendly service.   Good vegetarian options.

My photo is blurry because I only took a boomerang (sorry 😅) but it was so yummy! And I would absolutely recommend for nice little date night or dinner with friends! The only reason I’m not giving 5 stars is because our table was extremely small and awkwardly in the middle of all the foot traffic. A little overwhelming.
I had the chicken Tagine whilst I was here last. Delicious and herby, the jasmine rice was super fragrant. Can’t wait to come back! You won’t be disappointed. :)
Nice staff and delicious food!
Wow, the lamb burger is divine, cooked to perfection, I give this restaurant a hundred stars!
I LOVE QUEEN! Food is so yummy and the staff/owners are the most friendly, fun and hospitable. Can’t go wrong with a classic falafel sandwich and a side of fries!

So thankful they are still open knowing this year has been hard for local businesses.  I remember when they were on the corner attached to House of Yes and getting ready to move to their current location. When they finally did it was such a treat! The menu expanded to better suit indoor dining while maintaining the flavors I had come to love.  At the beginning of the pandemic we would go once a week for take-out to support and get our fix of good food. My favorite is the Chicken Shawarma Sandwich. The pickled cauliflower and grilled onions are a perfect marriage of flavors.  My partner loves the Shakshuka. Harissa, eggs, tahini, and grilled pita: what's not to love? Served hot with a bit of spice. If he doesn't get this he really enjoys the Lamb Burger for a meal on the go. It's hearty and still with a kick of harissa.  If you do go, work your way through the menu to find your favorite. I've had everything here and was not disappointed.  As a side note: the owners have been really diligent in maintaining the safety of their guests and staff during the pandemic. Masks, gloves, sanitizer, and distancing are all spot on. Cannot wait to be able to sit down in their beautiful space again, though doing take-out makes me really happy.

Cool atmosphere for relaxing or hang out with your friends. The crew is always quick, informative and super kind. Such good vibes.  Food is awesome, I have tried almost everything on the menu and ever disappointed. Also it includes lots of delicious vegan options :)
I had my first ever experience with trying Mediterranean food here and it was great! Always stoked to find new places with vegetarian options that actually taste good. Super friendly atmosphere
Their falafel is amazing as is the service and environment. Thank you for the delicious meal! Will be back again soon.

My favorite spot in Bushwick. Cute and friendly vibes, yummy cocktails (get the hibiscus marg!) and a mouthwatering lamb burger served in a pita that I crave on the reg. Also the pitas are super fluffy and delicious. Big recc.
The most delicious food ever!! Honestly .. these flavors are something else. Every dish tastes so fresh and amazing! Queen is Queen 🌟
This place is delicious. I chose to eat my birthday dinner here because the food is filled with Love!!
Sometimes I have dreams about the lamb burgers with cheese. The cravings are real.

We ordered the sabich sandwich, falafel plate, beet salad, fries, and hibiscus drink. All were delicious to the last bite/sip. The place seemed slammed with takeaway orders, but they were still able to whip everything out in fifteen minutes. The server was courteous and entertaining. Plus, the bathrooms were clean. Loved my experience. I'm coming back tomorrow.

Absolutely obsessed with this place- definitely my go-to for healthy nourishment that is delicious and perfectly spiced with all those fab middle eastern flavors.  I don't often eat meat, but when I do... Its usually to go here and have the chicken tagine (lemon herb version!). Shakshuka, butternut squash soup and the little gem salad are my usual faves. My vegan friends love this place too, and that's saying a lot because they are so super picky ;)
Food here is really really great! Try the schnitzel sandwich it is 🔥🔥🔥🔥🔥. The music and vibe is perfect here, and the people who work here are sweet and funny too. Highly recommended!

QUEEN IS THE BEST! <3 the food really makes me feel at home. The salads are always on point, the falafel is super yum, hummus is so good!! I'm also obsessed with the fact that they have amba. I love getting egg sandwiches with labane, or the beet salad. They are great and have lots of vegetarian options 🌱Also the drinks are dope ✨friendly and awesome people too! DEF EAT HERE ❤️❤️❤️❤️

This little gem is the Queen of MY MOUTH. I crave the salads on a regular basis, and the hummus is the gold standard, (believe me, I’ve known a lot of hummuses) Great ambiance, lots of memories made there.  Recommended with complete enthusiasm!
Super tasty food, amazing drinks and super friendly service.
Very good food and great music.
Not sure what’s going on with the tagine but it was basically oily soup. I love olive oil but this was not good.

I was a bit worried about some of the reviews but I'm so glad I ordered from this place. The food was PHENOMENAL. We ordered the chicken shawarma plate and baba ghanoush and it was sooo delicious. Everything tastes very fresh and the ingredients are excellent quality, it was just like, if not better than homemade! Usually Shwarma feels like junk food but this one was very clean and tastes healthy. I also loved the compostable eco friendly packaging, very impressed with this place. My only complaint is I wish the portion size was slightly bigger just so I could enjoy more deliciousness. Do not hesitate to frequent this place if you love authentic middle eastern food!
Very delicious! Great lamb burger if you eat in (it doesn't deliver well), the shawarma is great too.

I have low threshold for seamless orders but this was absolutely terrible. The food arrived freezing cold and late. Overpriced and the portion size was tiny for a $15 chicken shawarma.  Barely any chicken. The chicken that was there tasted like fish. Please avoid!

Lovely little place. The aesthetic here is BEAUTIFUL, I would like to sleep here lol. Awesome drink selection. Great customer service. Everything is packaged so well!!!!!! Awesome delicious yummy food.
They have one of the best, most flavorful falafels. I go there specifically for that, among many of their other appealing factors.
Ordered delivery a few weeks ago and I was super impressed. The chicken tangine with preserved lemons was out of control I’m STILL thinking about it.
This is the second time the food came iced cold.  Not even lukewarm, completely cold.   No matter how good the food is, I just can't enjoy it that cold.  Sad ... very sad....

So I’ve ordered a few times from here through Seamless-  Not only is it absolutely delicious  The service is so great  I see why they got five stars!!  My favorite spot in Brooklyn and I’m very very picky  During a pandemic m- these people are still thriving and delivering delicious food!!!

As a vegetarian, Queen is one of the only restaurants in Bushwick I can go to and know there are LOTS of options on the menu. Healthy, too. My favorite dishes are the Little Gem Salad and the Butternut Squash Soup. I LOVE the decor inside too, so cozy!

I ordered through Uber Eats in a hangry state, so I was really taking a chance on a place I’d never been before. Had the falafel hummus and gem salad. Everything was excellent, very yummy, sauces and all (green was a little spicy, to be expected). I also never order drinks but I ordered a Queen half & half with the intention of mixing it with an adult beverage and ended up drinking it straight. It was fresh, just sweetened enough but not over the top, full spring of fresh mint. I look forward to ordering from here again and maybe visiting the restaurant.
Bartender was an absolute delight—she makes a hell of a drink.

The bigger new Queen (formerly Queen of Falafel, if I am not mistaken) doesn't disappoint.  Order at the window and take with you or sit at one of the several tables.  The price is ...hip brooklyn - but not EXPENSIVE.  The staff is just friendly, nice, cool.  Alcohalic and non available - and on the non side some pretty interesting (and tasty) choices.
delicious- both my kids and love their fries and their sandwiches are pretty yummy, too- order the sabich sandwich with pickles!

Chicken shawarma platter is really bland tasting with no flavor. The only decent part was the cucumber salad. The chicken was burnt to the point where it was carcinogenic.  It was definitely not fresh either. Tasted very stale. The soup was alright (just had a few sips). The hummus was good but it definitely didn't redeem the rest of the meal. I liked the pita chips despite them almost breaking my teeth. Oh and we both got diarrhea after eating this food. Don't be fooled by the nice pictures I took of the food. I'm just trying to be detailed.

Came across this place today and loved it!  They’re doing a great job with the Covid regulations...tables were distanced outside, menu on QR code in table, order & pay online so very limited contact. Servers bring food to table and food came out quickly.  Yum!  We had the sesame chicken sandwich with French fries and kicking aioli!  We ordered hibiscus margaritas and fresh lemonade with vodka-so good!  The staff was very friendly and took time to answer questions. The owners are Moroccan-Israeli and have brought great food to the neighborhood.
Very good food .. and Evey dish has delicious taste .
I like steak on the rare side but the lamb was too rare, not properly cooked inside.  Other customers took theirs back.  My friends falafel dish was delicious.
I can’t say enough about this place . Food is fantastic! Try the hummus ! It  for real!

Ordered chicken schnitzel sandwich it took ages to be served  we sat at a table it’s comes in a pita bread( sandwich  is 2 slices of bread ) it was soggy served in a paper bag didn’t come with a plate even though we sat outside it was not take away.  Staff is indifferent 😐 staff and kitchen needs training  to understand what a sandwich is ?  no where to the standard of other places in NY
Great service. Delicious food. Go and support them!

The falafel is absolutely delicious, everything we ordered was fantastic. The staff were also LOVELY and dealing so well with the craziness of operating during shifting COVID regulations and the battles trying to serve people outdoors on a very busy Bushwick street. Totally recommended

The outdoor seating is limited but nicely put together. The lady with the pink hair was very nice, helpful and took care of cleaning the tables and doing the drinks, it seems common sense, but not all restaurants keep an eye on the cleaning of the tables.

We had the chicken schwarma, lamb burger, falafel and pita chips.. All really good.  The lamb was not dry at all and not gamey like lamb burgers can be.. just right.  The pita chips were fresh!  Very nice people running the place too. Happy to have discovered this we will be back soon.

Why change what wasn’t broken? I miss queen of falafel —- I would eat there multiple times a month (well get takeout). Only went to this place once was not impressed by falafel anymore they changed menu in a bad way, imo. Please lmk if you bring back the old you
Sidewalk seating that isn't terrible, in the shade, with good wifi and great iced tea is a rare find in the pandemic. Also the falafel is killer
Great Food

Came here today with gf for some food and drinks. Everything was really good. Good food good drinks and amazing service. We ordered the chicken shawarma platter, hibiscus margarita and the rum fruit punch.
Great food and service. Best falafel ever! Affordable prices!

Open for takeout during the pandemic. Friendly helpful staff. Ordered the Falafel Sandwich, Hummus Plate and Gem Salad with Beets. Falafel was excellent. Hummus was nice with some oil added on top. The pitas were thick and chewy. I prefer the thinner type to dip, but these were fresh and tasty. The Gem salad was pretty basic, wouldn’t reorder, but the beets had a lovely citrus topping and would probably order them alone as a side.
If it was ok to live on only hummus I would never eat any place else.
Food is always fresh and with lots of flavors. For me the quality of the food is a level above the other places I usually order in Bushwick.  Prices are also very reasonable.
The only thing I can say is wow the food has so much flavor taste and spices it is amazing.
Quick, courteous and friendly service! And if you are looking for AUTHENTIC middle eastern food - THIS IS THE SPOT YOU BEEN LOOKING FOR
Amazing Falafel..
Delicious and flavorful food. Great vegetarian options.
DELICIOUS food!’ And this comes from a table of middle eastern food lovers. Fresh, nourishing, tasty and delicious.

Nice little restaurant for a healthy alternative. Very intimate and in a great location. They don't have a liquor license so it isn't possible to get a drink with your meal. Friendly staff and great atmosphere. Would highly recommend!
Nice and fresh food
Super
Hands down the best, freshest, perfectly cooked falafel EVER...at least in the city. The bread is freshly baked too, so good.

Pretty good food, kindly staff and cheap price in a cozy place. The food is super heathy, totally homemade. I ate a marvelous lentil soup (it could be a little bit bigger) and a falafel kebab (the falafel was a little bit harder than it should to be perfect, but it is totally worth of ordering). Almost all options are vegan or vegetarian.
Great vibe great food
I love this place! The food is fantastic and they're open late! Try the schnitzel, shawarma and hibiscus tea!
Beautiful restaurant and food. Exceptional quality. Staff is always warm. :)

(Translated by Google) We had lunch there with 4 friends and were all overwhelmed. The food was fabulous, the service friendly and professional and the decor was great. I will return very quickly and without hesitation!  (Original) Nous y avons déjeuné avec 4 amies et étions toutes comblées. La nourriture était fabuleuse, le service amical et professionnel et la deco est super. J’y retournerai très vite et sans hésiter !
friendly staff, you can order humus with pita-like thingy with cheaper price
Amazing food, great service and beautiful place

Great hummus and pita. The hummus was especially phenomenal. Wasn't a huge fan of my shroom shawarma, each piece individually was great but something about all the elements together didn't work for me. Love the atmosphere, relaxed not too stuffy Moroccan atmosphere, and the other food I had was great so I'll definitely be going back.  The price point is just what the wyckoff strip needed, great casual spot with solid vibes to hang out and relax. Will be great when things warm up.
Fluffy soft pitas, great tehini, the falafels are great! New location with sitting areas! Kewl design! I'm definitely coming back.

The food was beautifully presented, delicious, and smelled amazing. The menu also has many vegan options. But, they are small portions for the price you pay. Although, I had a 10 dollar salad that was pretty large and filling. The fries and aioli were  particularly yummy. Everytime I ate one I wanted another. I don't feel that way about all fries. I wish I would have also tried the falafel  because it look very good. I gave it 4 stars because they forgot about someones order and it took a long time to get and pay the bill. Food service was fast. Waiter service was slow.
Their falafel pitta bread was stunning and the service was great.

Best hummus I’ve ever had. All the dishes are fresh, full of flavor, light and lots of aroma. The shallots and fresh herbs on the lentil soup gave it an beautiful presentation  as well as delicious bite. And the beets, so clean and lovely. Everything is visually and tastefully done!
So glad this place reopened! Its beautiful inside + great new options!

Love how quaint and warm this place is. Came here on a Saturday night around 9 and we absolutely loved our meal. We ordered the babaganoush to start and got two sandwiches; the falafel and chicken schwarma. I must note that these are my usual go-to comfort foods and I'm normally a tough critic when it comes to these foods but both were so tasty!! I was truly impressed! Would definitely order those sandwiches again!!! Also a great plus, no reservation was needed and the staff was incredibly nice to us.
Love this place! Decor is nice. Food is great, they’re very polite, and service is quick. Haven’t tried anything I didn’t like.
One of the best Mediterranean places I’ve ever been to. Had the falafel and lamb burger wrapped in pita. Still thinking about it several hours later. Can’t wait to go back!
Amazing food and ambient. Best hummus I have had in the USA. Great prices and amazing service. Make sure when you come to ask for the specials!
So so so good. I always get their eggplant sandwich. It has everything I love combined - gooey eggplant, egg, potato, tahini sauce, tomato.... Diviiiiine

Absolutely amazing falafel--all fava! Homemade warm and pillowy pitas. I had the chicken schnitzel- was a little confused about the name but it was wonderful! Crispy thin pounded chicken in the aforementioned pita. Pro tip: get some harissa on the side for a little spice. Not to mention super warm and inviting ambiance, and friendly service/companionship from Jess and Luis! Excellent all around.

I was super excited to find out the “queen” reopened right out side my house with my favorite dishes! No need to shlep anywhere else anymore. And apparently I was the first one to try the Tangier so double down on the excitement.
Incredible food and good portions (especially the hummus). If you have leftovers, get a few extra pita to go.  Can't wait to try the bar.
Amazing food !! Great stuff

(Translated by Google) Good atmosphere and excellent service. The falafel is very tasty and homemade! Very good service and tasty falafel. I completely recommended.  (Original) Buen ambiente y un excelente servicio. El falafel está muy rico y es casero! Very good service and tasty falafel. I completely recommended.
